AWS WAF is a web application firewall that protects your web applications from common web exploits and attacks like SQL injection, XSS, and DDoS.

XSS protection means preventing Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks
XSS is when an attacker injects malicious JavaScript into a web application, which then runs in other users’ browsers.

🔵 How WAF Works

User Request
     │
     ▼
AWS WAF
     │
     ├── Check rules
     │
     ├── Malicious request → BLOCK ❌
     └── Normal request    → ALLOW ✅
     │
     ▼
Your Application
(Safe!) ✅

🔵 What WAF Protects Against

SQL Injection        → Block DB attacks ✅
XSS                  → Block script injection ✅
DDoS                 → Block flood attacks ✅
Bad Bots             → Block scrapers ✅
IP Blacklisting      → Block specific IPs ✅
Geo Blocking         → Block specific countries ✅
Rate Limiting        → Block too many requests ✅
