================================================
  AWS WAF — SETUP NOTES
================================================

[ WHAT WAF PROTECTS ]
  SQL Injection        → attacker sends: ' OR 1=1--
  XSS                  → attacker sends: <script>steal()</script>
  HTTP Flood           → 1000 bots × 100 req/min
  Bot traffic          → fake browser requests
  Geo blocking         → block entire countries
  Rate limiting        → block IPs sending too fast
  Custom rules         → your own block/allow logic

------------------------------------------------

[ STEP 1 — Open WAF Console ]
  AWS Console → search "WAF" → AWS WAF & Shield
  
  Make sure region is correct:
    CloudFront  → must use us-east-1 (global)
    ALB/NLB     → use your resource region (us-east-2)

------------------------------------------------

[ STEP 2 — Create Web ACL ]
  WAF Console → Web ACLs → Create Web ACL

  Fill in:
    Name:         my-waf-web-acl
    Description:  WAF for production app
    Region:       your region (or CloudFront global)
    
  Associated resources:
    → Add your ALB / CloudFront / API Gateway here
    → Can also add later

------------------------------------------------

[ STEP 3 — Add Rule Groups ]
  This is the most important step.
  Rules = what WAF actually blocks.

  Option A — AWS Managed Rules (recommended, free)
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Click: Add rules → Add managed rule groups
  
  Enable these:
    ✅ AWSManagedRulesCommonRuleSet
       Blocks: SQLi, XSS, bad requests
       
    ✅ AWSManagedRulesKnownBadInputsRuleSet  
       Blocks: Log4j, malformed requests
       
    ✅ AWSManagedRulesSQLiRuleSet
       Blocks: SQL injection specifically
       
    ✅ AWSManagedRulesAmazonIpReputationList
       Blocks: Known bad IPs, bots, scrapers
       
    ✅ AWSManagedRulesBotControlRuleSet
       Blocks: Automated bot traffic
       NOTE: Extra cost — $10/month + $1/million req

  Option B — Custom Rules (your own logic)
  ──────────────────────────────────────────
  Click: Add rules → Add my own rules

  Example 1 — Rate limit per IP:
    Rule name:   RateLimitLogin
    Type:        Rate based rule
    Rate limit:  2000 requests per 5 minutes
    Scope:       URI path starts with /login
    Action:      Block ✅

  Example 2 — Geo block:
    Rule name:   BlockCountries
    Type:        Regular rule
    Condition:   Country is NOT IN [IN, US, GB]
    Action:      Block ✅

  Example 3 — Block bad User-Agent:
    Rule name:   BlockBadBots
    Type:        Regular rule
    Condition:   User-Agent contains "sqlmap"
    Action:      Block ✅

------------------------------------------------

[ STEP 4 — Set Default Action ]
  At bottom of Web ACL creation:
  
  Default action:
    Allow  → allow all traffic not matched by rules ✅
    Block  → block all traffic not matched by rules
    
  Choose: ALLOW (most common)
  WAF only blocks what matches your rules

------------------------------------------------

[ STEP 5 — Review and Create ]
  Review all rules → Create Web ACL
  Takes 1-2 minutes to deploy

------------------------------------------------

[ STEP 6 — Associate with Resource ]
  If not done in Step 2:
  
  WAF Console → Web ACLs → select your ACL
  → Associated AWS resources → Add
  → Select your ALB / CloudFront / API Gateway

  For Shield Advanced:
  Shield Console → Protected Resources
  → Select resource → Associate WAF Web ACL

------------------------------------------------

[ STEP 7 — Enable Logging ]
  WAF Console → Web ACLs → select ACL
  → Logging and metrics → Enable logging
  
  Send logs to:
    → S3 bucket (cheapest)
    → CloudWatch Logs (real time)
    → Kinesis Firehose (analytics)

  Logs show:
    Which rule blocked the request
    Source IP
    URI path
    Timestamp

------------------------------------------------

[ IMPORTANT — WAF COSTS ]
  Web ACL:          $5/month per ACL
  Rule group:       $1/month per rule
  Requests:         $0.60 per 1 million requests
  Bot Control:      $10/month + $1/million req
  
  Managed rules:    FREE (no extra cost)
  Custom rules:     $1/month each

------------------------------------------------

[ WAF vs SHIELD — REMEMBER ]
  WAF alone     → blocks SQLi, XSS, bad bots ✅
                  rate limits per IP ✅
                  NOT enough for large DDoS ❌

  Shield Std    → L3 & L4 DDoS, free, auto ✅
  Shield Adv    → L3, L4 & L7 DDoS + WAF ✅

  WAF + Shield  → complete production security ✅

